abstract: The president’s re-election campaign may offer some surprises in its pitch to American voters.
snippet: The president’s re-election campaign may offer some surprises in its pitch to American voters.
lead_paragraph: Addressing his cheering supporters in New Hampshire, Bernie Sanders declared, “This victory here is the beginning of the end for Donald Trump.”

abstract: Between Bernie Sanders’s win (but not by much), Amy Klobuchar’s strong third and Joe Biden’s leaving before the polls closed, the hosts saw lots of room for interpretation.

abstract: A campaign of sponsored content for the candidate flourished suddenly on Instagram. A new outfit, called Meme 2020, is behind it.
snippet: A campaign of sponsored content for the candidate flourished suddenly on Instagram. A new outfit, called Meme 2020, is behind it.
lead_paragraph: Mike Bloomberg has contracted some of the biggest meme-makers on the internet to post sponsored content on Instagram promoting his presidential campaign.

snippet: Coronavirus, Pope Francis, Roger Stone: Here’s what you need to know.
lead_paragraph: Coronavirus cases had seemed to be leveling off, but then new numbers showed the largest one-day increase recorded so far. abstract: Help wanted, and it’s named Ralph.
snippet: Help wanted, and it’s named Ralph.
lead_paragraph: Perhaps you think New Hampshire sent us a mixed message. After all, Bernie Sanders won but the moderates got more votes, and on Tuesday night three different candidates seemed to be giving victory speeches.

abstract: Nearly 300,000 people cast ballots in the Democratic primary, far surpassing the 2016 turnout and breaking a record set in 2008.
snippet: Nearly 300,000 people cast ballots in the Democratic primary, far surpassing the 2016 turnout and breaking a record set in 2008.
lead_paragraph: In Iowa last week, Democrats looking anxiously for a surge in caucus turnout — higher, some expected, than the record set in 2008 — were dismayed when the numbers barely even exceeded the much lower bar set in 2016.

headline_main: New Hampshire Primary Sets a Record for Turnout, but It May Be Deceiving
headline_print_headline: In Turnout, The Numbers Are Higher, But Deceptive

abstract: Mr. Sanders’s victory in the New Hampshire primary and his strengths in the 2020 race are worrying moderates who fear he could cost Democrats the presidency and the House in the fall.
snippet: Mr. Sanders’s victory in the New Hampshire primary and his strengths in the 2020 race are worrying moderates who fear he could cost Democrats the presidency and the House in the fall.
lead_paragraph: CHATTANOOGA, Tenn. — As Senator Bernie Sanders and his supporters reveled in his victory in the New Hampshire primary on Tuesday, Jimmy Tawater’s mood was less celebratory.
